# PCR Primer Validation - Enrique Herrera (NMRC)
# Input:
#	FASTA file, contigs from assembly
#	Primers, listed in strict FASTA format:
#	>forward
#	ATGCGCGCTACTTCGATCGAT
#	>reverse
#	GGCTCTGGGCTATAGGCTCCA
#
# Output:
#	To STDOUT, either an alignment location on the contig, or 'PCR Failure'
#
# Usage:
#	perl validate_primers.pl <reference.fasta>  <primers.fa> <num_MAX_MISMATCHES> <num_of_CPU>
## 1. the assembled genome i.e. a set of contigs
## 2. the primers file in strict fasta format
## 3. the max number of Mismatch between assembled genome and primer (default: 1)
## 4. num_of_CPU:  blast cpu usage

